vice Lines), with **Starlink Subscriber ARPU** as the key revenue metric.\n*   **For Enterprise & Government:** The primary metric is **revenue**. The documents state:\n    > "Enterprise and government revenue had an increase of $126 million [Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025]... growth in our aviation, maritime, and other enterprise business of $209 million..."\n*   **Retention Indicator (Enterprise):** A qualitative metric is provided: "**Since 2023, no Starlink Enterprise customer having contributed more than $750,000 of annual revenue has voluntarily discontinued their service.**" This suggests high retention but does not quantify the number of accounts.\n\n## **Summary**\nThe documents carefully **separate** consumer and enterprise/government customer metrics. There is **no unified "supported accounts" figure for Starlink**. The consumer segment is tracked by **Starlink Subscribers (Service Lines)**, while the enterprise/government segment is tracked by **revenue**, not account numbers. The term "supported accounts" is exclusively associated with the X/Grok AI platform.',
